results.question: What is seven-sided boundary spreading with the hydraulicborder spreading plate?
results.model_answer:
[Image] Hydraulic border spreading plate

Drive along the field edge when one-sided boundary spreading and send the flow of fertiliser granules with the hydraulic border spreading plate (optional extra). The working width on the side of the field edge can be adjusted by changing the hydraulic border spreading plate (optional extra).

Direction (1) (environmental setting)
Spread less to the field edge.
This will decrease the loss over the field edge, but the cover will not be as good

Direction (9) (yield setting)
Spread more to the field edge.
Cover is better, but the loss is greater

The maximum acceptable loss over the field edge is determined by environment standards. In order to comply with the standard the quantity of fertiliser spread beyond the field edge must be a maximum of 10% of the quantity distributed in the centre behind the spreader (= 100%). Test if the border spreading plate (optional extra) door de test therefore always before hand as described in paragraph "Testing the spreading pattern of the hydraulic border spreading plate" on page 84.
[Image]
